Reasoning: 
1) cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper involves image processing and feature extraction from clothing images, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2) cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with organizing and analyzing a large-scale clothing dataset, which involves information retrieval techniques. 
3) cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for discovering clothing attributes, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
4) cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with processing and analyzing multimedia data (clothing images) and extracting features from them. 
5) cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper involves studying consumer behavior and trends in clothing consumption, which falls under the domain of social and information networks.
